Introduction

ODD EYE CIRCLE (also shortened as OEC) started as the second sub-unit of the girl group LOONA. The unit consisted of Kim Lip, JinSoul, and Choerry. They made their official debut on September 21, 2017, with their mini album "Mix & Match."

The sub-unit explores themes of love, energy, and intimacy. The three members emphasize taking proactive steps in love rather than waiting passively. Each member possesses unique abilities: Kim Lip can travel through time, JinSoul can traverse space, and Choerry has a connection to mirrors, allowing her to move between different worlds.

The sub-unit went on hiatus following the full-group debut of LOONA in 2018. However, in September 2022, they eventually made their Japanese debut as ODD EYE CIRCLE+, with the addition of Heejin.

In November 2022, the members of LOONA began filing lawsuits to suspend their contracts with their agency, Blockberry Creative. Following this, in January 2023, it was reported that the members of ODD EYE CIRCLE won their lawsuits and effectively left the agency.

Three months after leaving Blockberry Creative, it was revealed that Kim Lip, JinSoul, Choerry, and Heejin signed exclusive contracts with MODHAUS, much to the fans' delight. This news was followed by rumors that MODHAUS filed trademark applications to obtain the name 'ODD EYE CIRCLE.'

By June of 2023, MODHAUS announced that ODD EYE CIRCLE will return to promotions through the ARTMS project, also known as 'The Artemis Strategy.' The group made their highly anticipated comeback under MODHAUS on July 12th, 2023 with the release of their 6-track EP, "ODD EYE CIRCLE " alongside a MV for the track "Air Force One".

The group released a digital single of an English re-recording of their debut song "Sweet Crazy Love", released on November 24th, 2023.
